      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/validation/vr-stiffness-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — FEA vs. bench (N=11)",
      "description": "FEA-predicted construct stiffness compared against experimental measurements from 11 non-cannulated pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. Mean percent difference 4.2%; E/uval = 0.87, satisfying the <10% and <1.96 acceptance criteria. A Monte Carlo UQ campaign (n=500 Latin-hypercube samples) was executed to propagate material-property and geometric uncertainty through the model ensemble; results confirmed that prediction intervals envelope all experimental observations. Sensitivity indices from the UQ campaign identified cortical bone modulus and screw-rod contact friction as dominant contributors to stiffness variability."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/validation/vr-yield-force-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Yield force QoI comparison — FEA vs. bench (N=11)",
      "description": "FEA-predicted yield force compared against experimental yield force measurements. Mean percent difference 6.1%; E/uval = 1.14, within acceptance bounds. The UQ campaign described in the stiffness validation result also covered yield force outputs; Sobol sensitivity indices are tabulated in the supporting technical report (Nagaraja et al., 2023)."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/validation/vr-40mm-force-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Force at 40 mm displacement QoI comparison — FEA vs. bench (N=11)",
      "description": "FEA-predicted force at 40 mm displacement compared against experimental values. Mean percent difference 7.8%; E/uval = 1.51, within acceptance bounds. Combined with stiffness and yield force results, overall model credibility is supported at the Medium assurance level for the stated COU."
    }
  ],
