      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening validated for Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw alloy; frictional contact formulation consistent with ASTM F1717 fixture geometry.",
      "rationale": "The continuum elastoplastic model with bilinear isotropic hardening is well-established for titanium alloy implant components under quasi-static loading. Frictional contact between screw and rod, and between construct and UHMWPE vertebral body surrogate, is represented with penalty-based contact consistent with prior published validation studies. Model form uncertainty is moderate and bounded by the UQ campaign results."
    },
    {
