      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test specimens; specimens sourced from same production lot as computational model inputs; dimensional inspection confirms geometric conformance.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested, meeting the N≥10 criterion. All specimens were drawn from the same production lot as the material characterization coupons, ensuring traceability. Dimensional inspection of screw outer diameter, thread pitch, and rod diameter confirmed conformance to nominal CAD geometry within ±0.05 mm."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least two independent test conditions (e.g., loading rate, surrogate material) to bracket COU operating range.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 standard condition (quasi-static, 5 mm/min crosshead speed, room temperature). Although this condition is representative of the regulatory submission standard, only one test condition was explored, falling below the required level of 3 for a Medium model risk COU. This is the one identified gap in the credibility assessment and is noted as an accepted residual limitation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Computational model inputs (geometry, material, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to physical test specimen and fixture configuration.",
      "rationale": "CAD geometry used in the FEA was derived from the same product drawings as the manufactured test specimens. Boundary conditions replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture constraints (fixed inferior block, axially loaded superior block at 5° offset). Material inputs were measured from the same production lot. Equivalency is documented in the V&V plan and confirmed by the independent review."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% for all three QoIs; statistical equivalence confirmed across both laboratories.",
      "rationale": "For all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement), E/uval ranged from 0.87 to 1.51 and percent differences ranged from 4.2% to 7.8%, satisfying both acceptance criteria. Inter-laboratory variability was assessed using an F-test (p=0.43), confirming no statistically significant difference between the two testing sites."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
