      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) directly correspond to regulatory acceptance criteria specified in ASTM F1717 and FDA guidance.",
      "rationale": "The three selected QoIs are explicitly required by ASTM F1717 and are the metrics evaluated in FDA 510(k) submissions for pedicle screw systems. They directly characterize the structural performance attributes most relevant to clinical failure modes (fatigue initiation, construct loosening). QoI relevance is therefore high and well-established in the regulatory literature."
    },
