    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/org/depuy-synthes-computational-mechanics",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels for a Medium model risk, Medium assurance COU. The single gap (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted because the single ASTM F1717 test condition is the regulatory standard condition and no alternative conditions are specified in the submission scope. Overall E/uval values across all three QoIs are well within the 1.96 threshold, and inter-laboratory consistency is confirmed. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending.",
